  "text": "I'm very sorry for your loss. Grief is heavy and personal, and it’s natural to feel overwhelmed, confused, and aching. Be gentle with yourself and allow whatever feelings come without judgment — Ra reminds us that love and presence are the most healing things you can offer yourself and the one you lost.\n\n\n\nRa also offers a comforting perspective about the continuity of the self: in important ways nothing of true spiritual significance is lost at death, and the inner qualities of the one you love become more apparent, not less.\n\n\n\nPractically: allow grieving in small, safe ways (write to your mother, speak aloud what you miss, keep simple daily rituals of remembrance), reach out for support when you need it, and practice brief moments of centering breath or loving-kindness to soothe raw emotions. If you’d like, tell me a little about her and I can suggest a short ritual or phrase you might use to feel connected.",
  "quotes": [
    {
      "text": "Questioner: Have I missed anything now that we can do at all to aid the instrument during, before, or after a session or at any time? Ra: I am Ra. The love and devotion of this group misses nothing. Be at peace. There is some toll for this work. This instrument embraces this or we could not speak. Rest then in that peace and love and do as you will, as you wish, as you feel. Let there be an end to worry when this is accomplished. The great healer of distortions is love.",
      "reference": "Ra 62.26",
      "url": "https://lawofone.info/s/62#26"
    },
    {
      "text": "Questioner: Is there any loss to the mind or spirit after this transition which we call death or any impairment of either because of the loss of this chemical body that we now have? Ra: I am Ra. In your terms there is a great loss of mind complex due to the fact that much of the activity of a mental nature of which you are aware during the experience of this space/time continuum is as much of a surface illusion as is the chemical body complex. \n\n In other terms nothing whatever of importance is lost; the character or, shall we say, pure distillation of emotions and biases or distortions and wisdoms, if you will, becoming obvious for the first time, shall we say; these pure emotions and wisdoms and bias/distortions being, for the most part, either ignored or underestimated during physical life experience. \n\n In terms of the spiritual, this channel is then much opened due to the lack of necessity for the forgetting characteristic of third density.",
      "reference": "Ra 30.4",
      "url": "https://lawofone.info/s/30#4"
    }
  ],
  "suggestions": [
    "She was warm and funny; I’ll tell you about her.",
    "What helps me most right now is a short ritual or memory-sharing.",
    "I’d like to explore something else for a little while."
  ]
